com.psddev.dari.db
Class CachingDatabase

java.lang.Object
  com.psddev.dari.db.ForwardingDatabase
      com.psddev.dari.db.CachingDatabase
All Implemented Interfaces:
Database, SettingsBackedObject
public class CachingDatabase
extends ForwardingDatabase

Caches the results of read operations.

For example, given:

CachingDatabase caching = new CachingDatabase();
caching.setDelegate(Database.Static.getDefault());
PaginatedResult<Article> result = Query.from(Article.class).using(caching).select(0, 5);

These are some of the queries that won't trigger additional reads in the delegate database:

  • Query.from(Article.class).using(caching).count()
  • Query.from(Article.class).using(caching).where("_id = ?", result.getItems().get(0));

All methods are thread-safe.
